    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Steamed Fish</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 whole fish (such as tilapia or sea bass), cleaned and scaled</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon oyster sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon rice wine or dry sherry</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon sugar</li>
            <li>3 slices ginger</li>
            <li>2 green onions, sliced into strips</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Seafood</li>
            <li>Healthy</li>
            <li>Chinese</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Clean and scale the whole fish, making sure it is gutted. Pat it dry with paper towels.</li>
            <li>Place the fish on a heatproof plate that fits into your steamer.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, mix together soy sauce, oyster sauce, sesame oil, rice wine or sherry, and sugar. Pour this sauce over the fish.</li>
            <li>Place ginger slices on top of the fish, and sprinkle green onion strips over it.</li>
            <li>Bring water to a boil in the steamer. Once boiling, carefully place the plate with the fish into the steamer, ensuring that the water does not touch the fish.</li>
            <li>Steam the fish for about 12-15 minutes or until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.</li>
            <li>Garnish the steamed fish with fresh cilantro leaves.</li>
            <li>Serve the Steamed Fish over cooked white rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious and healthy Steamed Fish!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

